%% Session lifecycle, derived from docs/schemas/Session.schema.json's
%% `status` enum (ACTIVE, EXPIRED, CANCELLED, AUTH_REQUIRED, CLOSED) and
%% Chapter 40's expiry conditions (inactivity, confidence loss, user
%% command, authentication timeout, device lock, policy restrictions).
%%
%% Unlike Principal/Resource, Session.schema.json has no CREATED or
%% ARCHIVED state -- a session begins ACTIVE at `startedAt` and its
%% terminal states (Expired/Cancelled/Closed) are the closest equivalent
%% to "archived". Recorded as a documented finding in
%% Session-Schema.md, not silently invented here.
%% v0.7 Architecture Completion Phase, Priority 5.
stateDiagram-v2
[*] --> Active
Active --> AuthRequired
AuthRequired --> Active
AuthRequired --> Expired
AuthRequired --> Closed
Active --> Expired
Active --> Cancelled
Active --> Closed
Expired --> [*]
Cancelled --> [*]
Closed --> [*]
